-2-Returns:


make_reverse_iterator(ranges::next(ranges::begin(base_), ranges::end(base_)))



-3- Remarks: In order to provide the amortized constant time complexity required by the
range concept, this function caches the result within the reverse_view 
for use on subsequent calls.


constexpr reverse_iterator<iterator_t<V>> begin() requires common_range<V>;
constexpr auto begin() const requires common_range<const V>;




-4- Effects: Equivalent to: return make_reverse_iterator(ranges::end(base_));



